lernstick-config (82) lernstick-9; urgency=medium

  * [7d741f] All systems will renew their IP address via a simple DHCP renewal
    request when the lease time is still valid. Exact system clones will by
    default all use the same client identifier and this way succeed in getting
    all exactly the same IP address via DHCP renewal requests. This leads to a
    broken network during the lifetime of the first DHCP lease. We work around
    this problem by adding a NetworkManager config file to use the current MAC
    address of the hardware to generate a client identifier. This way even
    exact system clones will get a different IP address on different hardware.

 -- Ronny Standtke <ronny.standtke@gmx.net>  Sun, 04 Nov 2018 17:58:33 +0100

lernstick-config (81) lernstick-9; urgency=medium

  * [f61864] correctly remove old config file

